com.mapbox.api.directions.v5.models

Class Exclude

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mapbox.api.directions.v5.models.Exclude

  • public abstract class Exclude
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines excludes for RouteOptions.Builder.excludeObject(Exclude). This class provides type-safe way to read and build RouteOptions.exclude() parameter. All properties are strictly categorized after parsing. Unknown data types or flags are ignored. If you want to work with exclude criteria which is not yet supported, consider using raw RouteOptions.exclude() directly.

      • criteria

        @Nullable
public abstract java.util.List<java.lang.String> criteria()
        Exclude certain road types from routing. The default is to not exclude anything from the profile selected. The following exclude flags are available for each profile:

        DirectionsCriteria.PROFILE_DRIVING: One of DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_TOLL, DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_MOTORWAY, or DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_FERRY.

        DirectionsCriteria.PROFILE_DRIVING_TRAFFIC: One of DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_TOLL, DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_MOTORWAY, or DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_FERRY.

        DirectionsCriteria.PROFILE_WALKING: No excludes supported

        DirectionsCriteria.PROFILE_CYCLING: DirectionsCriteria.EXCLUDE_FERRY

        Returns:
        a list of strings matching one of the DirectionsCriteria.ExcludeCriteria exclusions

      • points

        @Nullable
public abstract java.util.List<com.mapbox.geojson.Point> points()
        Exclude certain points from routing. The default is to not exclude anything.
        Returns:
        a list of points excluded from the routing.
